				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A few hints for bazaar trading<a name="34388"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 13 04 10:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just a couple of things I've found.
<br />

<br />
First,  if you have an item that you have no idea for the value of then price it high.  Very high.  then watch to see if other items of similar value come on the market and how they get priced.  This assumes of course that the item you're selling didn't get snapped up in a hurry.  In that case what you thought was a high price may have been too low.  What can happen is that you'll see others setting their prices according to your prices.  It may even help to have two bazaar mules,  transfer the item over then underprice yourself.
<br />

<br />
Next,  know what NPC merchants will give you for items.  Don't price things lower than that as it's a wast of time.  You can often use this to make some extra cash however.  As an example,  I had an item that Merchants would give me 15 plat for with an unbuffed 75 Charisma.  I did a search and found a lrge number of people selling the item for less than that.  I bought up all of them with my bard,  put on my Charisma gear and sold them to a Merchant for a nice little profit.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
