				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A few hints for bazaar trading<a name="40859"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 20 04 12:33 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Mmmm, if you have no idea of the value of an item I would try a different approach.
<br />

<br />
1. Let's face it chances are that as a bard the item is easier for you to get than any other class who has to go through the hassle of grouping and rolling to get the item.
<br />

<br />
2. Just because someone is selling something at a price doesn't mean that anyone is buying at that price.
<br />

<br />
3. Some people like to buy up lower priced items and then try to sell them at a higher price. While at the appropriate level I would often get a dozen orc fang ear-rings for example and sell them all to one person who would then try to re-sell them. I made 500 plat in ten mins he may have made another 500 plat but in the time it took him to sell them I could go and get another dozen.
<br />

<br />
4. You want to sell lore items as quickly as possible so you can go kite another don't you? Not have them sitting in your bank for ages. Yes you can have several alts to hold things temporarily but there is still a limit.
<br />

<br />
Bards should sell at the lowest prices and still make the most money of any bazaar trader simply because your supply of good items is more certain and more numerous than anyone elses.
<br />

<br />
Therefore work out how much money you want to make per hour of play and price your sales according to how much time it took you to get it.
<br />

<br />
Of course as you can go get all the good stuff yourself you have nothing to spend all this money on anyway. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />. I run 7 (non bard) alts and I have more than enough with just the vendor trash loot I have picked up from the xp mobs to finance them all. I don't think any of them pay there own way though.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
