			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A few hints for bazaar trading<a name="43884"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 3 04 7:11 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Athelstan, I have no idea why you say bards can attain items easier?  Granted bards can solo some nice item camps, but there are plenty of other classes that can aquire a lot of items (necro and shaman come to mind) like that...  Item farming is hardly something only bards can do.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">One thing that I've found that sells good is Low Quality Rockhopper Hides. I've sold those things for 12 pp each. Go into MS and round up all the hoppers you can and fill up all the packs you can carry. I have no idea what those things are being used for but whatever it is they use a lot of them.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
They're used in leather paddings, which is needed for smithing.  You could possibly farm shadeling silks or spiderling silks (imo shadeling silks is easier and has the added bonus that shadow essence might drop off lesser shades), turn it into leather paddings (trivs at like 15), and sell the paddings, which are most likely worth 20pp each.  
<br />

<br />
As for bazaar selling, I do about the same.  If I have an item I don't know the value of, I look at the most important stats.  Say the item has a lot of int on it and pure casters can wear it, then I'll bazaar for other items that fit in that slot with the same int and look at them, if my item is about similar, I'll give it a similar price, but I'll always try high first.  Also make sure to look for recommended/required level, if yours doesn't have rec/req level, and the other items with similar stats do, price it higher than those.
<br />

<br />
When pricing items that are already available in the bazaar, it depends.  If I'm selling a popular item, that is bought often, I'll price it high enough, if it's an item I feel I'll ever be lucky of selling, I'll set it as the lowest price (and I don't do that 1pp lower than the other seller kind of thing<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> If I see someone selling an item only 1pp cheaper I'll buy the more expensive one, undercutting only 1pp on high pp items is silly if you ask me).  When dealing with items only one class can use, it's prolly gonna be harder to sell it too, so you might want to consider pricing it low enough too (especially true for bard only items on my server, even items that are relatively cheap stay up in trader for weeks it seems).
<br />

<br />
Another thing to note when selling items, if it's already available in the bazaar, but way overpriced (say a 10k item for 15k), and several people are selling it that expensive, I might price mine at 12500 (which is still too much, but when someone bazaars for it, sees 15k or more several times, and then 12.5k, they might buy it thinking they got a deal).  Most people who use the bazaar seem pretty clueless on the going price or how easy/difficult an item is to attain, they just buy at whatever the bazaar price is, so use that to your advantage in situations like this. :p
<br />

<br />
When buying items, bazaar for it a few days, but don't buy it unless you see it exceptionally cheap.  I'd also recommend hanging out in your server's auction channel, and keep an eye on prices.  Once you have a good idea of a fair going price, look for people selling it (or try sending tells to people selling it in the bazaar), and offer less than the going price, quite often you can make someone sell an item a lot cheaper, just keep haggling for it, and don't accept a price higher than the one you're going for.  This takes longer, but if you're patient and would rather get as much out of your money as possible, it's a great idea.  I've bought items that are worth 8k, for say 5k.  Often when you offer that, people will ask a higher price (say I offer 5k, they might say 6.5k), but just say no thanks, they'll drop it more.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> Some people really don't like it when you do that, but I see it as part of trading, and it's very rewarding to get an item at the price you set for, you might get to enjoy doing it a lot. ;)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
